{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01FRzW7VaDw8HC2DWxPLuXaW","type":"tool_result","content":"1\tpackage v1\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n5\t)\n6\t\n7\t// +genclient\n8\t// +genclient:nonNamespaced\n9\t// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n10\t// +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n11\t// +kubebuilder:resource:path=machineconfigurations,scope=Cluster\n12\t// +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n13\t// +openshift:api-approved.openshift.io=https://github.com/openshift/api/pull/1453\n14\t// +openshift:file-pattern=cvoRunLevel=0000_80,operatorName=machine-config,operatorOrdering=01\n15\t\n16\t// MachineConfiguration provides information to configure an operator to manage Machine Configuration.\n17\t//\n18\t// Compatibility level 1: Stable within a major release for a minimum of 12 months or 3 minor releases (whichever is longer).\n19\t// +openshift:compatibility-gen:level=1\n20\t// +openshift:validation:FeatureGateAwareXValidation:featureGate=BootImageSkewEnforcement,rule=\"self.?status.bootImageSkewEnforcementStatus.mode.orValue(\\\"\\\") == 'Automatic' ? self.?spec.managedBootImages.hasValue() || self.?status.managedBootImagesStatus.hasValue() : true\",message=\"when skew enforcement is in Automatic mode, a boot image configuration is required\"\n21\t// +openshift:validation:FeatureGateAwareXValidation:featureGate=BootImageSkewEnforcement,rule=\"self.?status.bootImageSkewEnforcementStatus.mode.orValue(\\\"\\\") == 'Automatic' ? !(self.?spec.managedBootImages.machineManagers.hasValue()) || size(self.spec.managedBootImages.machineManagers) > 0 : true\",message=\"when skew enforcement is in Automatic mode, managedBootImages.machineManagers must not be an empty list\"\n22\t// +openshift:validation:FeatureGateAwareXValidation:featureGate=BootImageSkewEnforcement,rule=\"self.?status.bootImageSkewEnforcementStatus.mode.orValue(\\\"\\\") == 'Automatic' ? !(self.?spec.managedBootImages.machineManagers.hasValue()) || !self.spec.managedBootImages.machineManagers.exists(m, m.resource == 'machinesets' && m.apiGroup == 'machine.openshift.io') || self.spec.managedBootImages.machineManagers.exists(m, m.resource == 'machinesets' && m.apiGroup == 'machine.openshift.io' && m.selection.mode == 'All') : true\",message=\"when skew enforcement is in Automatic mode, any MachineAPI MachineSet MachineManager must use selection mode 'All'\"\n23\t// +openshift:validation:FeatureGateAwareXValidation:featureGate=BootImageSkewEnforcement,rule=\"self.?status.bootImageSkewEnforcementStatus.mode.orValue(\\\"\\\") == 'Automatic' ? !(self.?status.managedBootImagesStatus.machineManagers.hasValue()) || self.status.managedBootImagesStatus.machineManagers.exists(m, m.selection.mode == 'All' && m.resource == 'machinesets' && m.apiGroup == 'machine.openshift.io'): true\",message=\"when skew enforcement is in Automatic mode, managedBootImagesStatus must contain a MachineManager opting in all MachineAPI MachineSets\"\n24\ttype MachineConfiguration struct {\n25\t\tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n26\t\n27\t\t// metadata is the standard object's metadata.\n28\t\t// More info: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md#metadata\n29\t\tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata\"`\n30\t\n31\t\t// spec is the specification of the desired behavior of the Machine Config Operator\n32\t\t// +required\n33\t\tSpec MachineConfigurationSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n34\t\n35\t\t// status is the most recently observed status of the Machine Config Operator\n36\t\t// +optional\n37\t\tStatus MachineConfigurationStatus `json:\"status\"`\n38\t}\n39\t\n40\ttype MachineConfigurationSpec struct {\n41\t\tStaticPodOperatorSpec `json:\",inline\"`\n42\t\n43\t\t// managedBootImages allows configuration for the management of boot images for machine\n44\t\t// resources within the cluster. This configuration allows users to select resources that should\n45\t\t// be updated to the latest boot images during cluster upgrades, ensuring that new machines\n46\t\t// always boot with the current cluster version's boot image. When omitted, this means no opinion\n47\t\t// and the platform is left to choose a reasonable default, which is subject to change over time.\n48\t\t// The default for each machine manager mode is All for GCP and AWS platforms, and None for all\n49\t\t// other platforms.\n50\t\t// +optional\n51\t\tManagedBootImages ManagedBootImages `json:\"managedBootImages\"`\n52\t\n53\t\t// nodeDisruptionPolicy allows an admin to set granular node disruption actions for\n54\t\t// MachineConfig-based updates, such as drains, service reloads, etc. Specifying this will allow\n55\t\t// for less downtime when doing small configuration updates to the cluster. This configuration\n56\t\t// has no effect on cluster upgrades which will still incur node disruption where required.\n57\t\t// +optional\n58\t\tNodeDisruptionPolicy NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig `json:\"nodeDisruptionPolicy\"`\n59\t\n60\t\t// irreconcilableValidationOverrides is an optional field that can used to make changes to a MachineConfig that\n61\t\t// cannot be applied to existing nodes.\n62\t\t// When specified, the fields configured with validation overrides will no longer reject changes to those\n63\t\t// respective fields due to them not being able to be applied to existing nodes.\n64\t\t// Only newly provisioned nodes will have these configurations applied.\n65\t\t// Existing nodes will report observed configuration differences in their MachineConfigNode status.\n66\t\t// +openshift:enable:FeatureGate=IrreconcilableMachineConfig\n67\t\t// +optional\n68\t\tIrreconcilableValidationOverrides IrreconcilableValidationOverrides `json:\"irreconcilableValidationOverrides,omitempty,omitzero\"`\n69\t\n70\t\t// bootImageSkewEnforcement allows an admin to configure how boot image version skew is\n71\t\t// enforced on the cluster.\n72\t\t// When omitted, this will default to Automatic for clusters that support automatic boot image updates.\n73\t\t// For clusters that do not support automatic boot image updates, cluster upgrades will be disabled until\n74\t\t// a skew enforcement mode has been specified.\n75\t\t// When version skew is being enforced, cluster upgrades will be disabled until the version skew is deemed\n76\t\t// acceptable for the current release payload.\n77\t\t// +openshift:enable:FeatureGate=BootImageSkewEnforcement\n78\t\t// +optional\n79\t\tBootImageSkewEnforcement BootImageSkewEnforcementConfig `json:\"bootImageSkewEnforcement,omitempty,omitzero\"`\n80\t}\n81\t\n82\t// BootImageSkewEnforcementConfig is used to configure how boot image version skew is enforced on the cluster.\n83\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.mode) && (self.mode =='Manual') ?  has(self.manual) : !has(self.manual)\",message=\"manual is required when mode is Manual, and forbidden otherwise\"\n84\t// +union\n85\ttype BootImageSkewEnforcementConfig struct {\n86\t\t// mode determines the underlying behavior of skew enforcement mechanism.\n87\t\t// Valid values are Manual and None.\n88\t\t// Manual means that the cluster admin is expected to perform manual boot image updates and store the OCP\n89\t\t// & RHCOS version associated with the last boot image update in the manual field.\n90\t\t// In Manual mode, the MCO will prevent upgrades when the boot image skew exceeds the\n91\t\t// skew limit described by the release image.\n92\t\t// None means that the MCO will no longer monitor the boot image skew. This may affect\n93\t\t// the cluster's ability to scale.\n94\t\t// This field is required.\n95\t\t// +unionDiscriminator\n96\t\t// +required\n97\t\tMode BootImageSkewEnforcementConfigMode `json:\"mode,omitempty\"`\n98\t\n99\t\t// manual describes the current boot image of the cluster.\n100\t\t// This should be set to the oldest boot image used amongst all machine resources in the cluster.\n101\t\t// This must include either the RHCOS version of the boot image or the OCP release version which shipped with that\n102\t\t// RHCOS boot image.\n103\t\t// Required when mode is set to \"Manual\" and forbidden otherwise.\n104\t\t// +optional\n105\t\tManual ClusterBootImageManual `json:\"manual,omitempty,omitzero\"`\n106\t}\n107\t\n108\t// ClusterBootImageManual is used to describe the cluster boot image in Manual mode.\n109\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.mode) && (self.mode =='OCPVersion') ?  has(self.ocpVersion) : !has(self.ocpVersion)\",message=\"ocpVersion is required when mode is OCPVersion, and forbidden otherwise\"\n110\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.mode) && (self.mode =='RHCOSVersion') ?  has(self.rhcosVersion) : !has(self.rhcosVersion)\",message=\"rhcosVersion is required when mode is RHCOSVersion, and forbidden otherwise\"\n111\t// +union\n112\ttype ClusterBootImageManual struct {\n113\t\t// mode is used to configure which boot image field is defined in Manual mode.\n114\t\t// Valid values are OCPVersion and RHCOSVersion.\n115\t\t// OCPVersion means that the cluster admin is expected to set the OCP version associated with the last boot image update\n116\t\t// in the OCPVersion field.\n117\t\t// RHCOSVersion means that the cluster admin is expected to set the RHCOS version associated with the last boot image update\n118\t\t// in the RHCOSVersion field.\n119\t\t// This field is required.\n120\t\t// +unionDiscriminator\n121\t\t// +required\n122\t\tMode ClusterBootImageManualMode `json:\"mode,omitempty\"`\n123\t\n124\t\t// ocpVersion provides a string which represents the OCP version of the boot image.\n125\t\t// This field must match the OCP semver compatible format of x.y.z. This field must be between\n126\t\t// 5 and 10 characters long.\n127\t\t// Required when mode is set to \"OCPVersion\" and forbidden otherwise.\n128\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.matches('^[0-9]+\\\\\\\\.[0-9]+\\\\\\\\.[0-9]+$')\",message=\"ocpVersion must match the OCP semver compatible format of x.y.z\"\n129\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxLength:=10\n130\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength:=5\n131\t\t// +optional\n132\t\tOCPVersion string `json:\"ocpVersion,omitempty\"`\n133\t\n134\t\t// rhcosVersion provides a string which represents the RHCOS version of the boot image\n135\t\t// This field must match rhcosVersion formatting of [major].[minor].[datestamp(YYYYMMDD)]-[buildnumber] or the legacy\n136\t\t// format of [major].[minor].[timestamp(YYYYMMDDHHmm)]-[buildnumber]. This field must be between\n137\t\t// 14 and 21 characters long.\n138\t\t// Required when mode is set to \"RHCOSVersion\" and forbidden otherwise.\n139\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.matches('^[0-9]+\\\\\\\\.[0-9]+\\\\\\\\.([0-9]{8}|[0-9]{12})-[0-9]+$')\",message=\"rhcosVersion must match format [major].[minor].[datestamp(YYYYMMDD)]-[buildnumber] or must match legacy format [major].[minor].[timestamp(YYYYMMDDHHmm)]-[buildnumber]\"\n140\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxLength:=21\n141\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength:=14\n142\t\t// +optional\n143\t\tRHCOSVersion string `json:\"rhcosVersion,omitempty\"`\n144\t}\n145\t\n146\t// ClusterBootImageManualMode is a string enum used to define the cluster's boot image in manual mode.\n147\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum:=\"OCPVersion\";\"RHCOSVersion\"\n148\ttype ClusterBootImageManualMode string\n149\t\n150\tconst (\n151\t\t// OCPVersion represents a configuration mode used to define the OCPVersion.\n152\t\tClusterBootImageSpecModeOCPVersion ClusterBootImageManualMode = \"OCPVersion\"\n153\t\n154\t\t// RHCOSVersion represents a configuration mode used to define the RHCOSVersion.\n155\t\tClusterBootImageSpecModeRHCOSVersion ClusterBootImageManualMode = \"RHCOSVersion\"\n156\t)\n157\t\n158\t// BootImageSkewEnforcementStatus is the type for the status object. It represents the cluster defaults when\n159\t// the boot image skew enforcement configuration is undefined and reflects the actual configuration when it is defined.\n160\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.mode) && (self.mode == 'Automatic') ?  has(self.automatic) : !has(self.automatic)\",message=\"automatic is required when mode is Automatic, and forbidden otherwise\"\n161\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.mode) && (self.mode == 'Manual') ?  has(self.manual) : !has(self.manual)\",message=\"manual is required when mode is Manual, and forbidden otherwise\"\n162\t// +union\n163\ttype BootImageSkewEnforcementStatus struct {\n164\t\t// mode determines the underlying behavior of skew enforcement mechanism.\n165\t\t// Valid values are Automatic, Manual and None.\n166\t\t// Automatic means that the MCO will perform boot image updates and store the\n167\t\t// OCP & RHCOS version associated with the last boot image update in the automatic field.\n168\t\t// Manual means that the cluster admin is expected to perform manual boot image updates and store the OCP\n169\t\t// & RHCOS version associated with the last boot image update in the manual field.\n170\t\t// In Automatic and Manual mode, the MCO will prevent upgrades when the boot image skew exceeds the\n171\t\t// skew limit described by the release image.\n172\t\t// None means that the MCO will no longer monitor the boot image skew. This may affect\n173\t\t// the cluster's ability to scale.\n174\t\t// This field is required.\n175\t\t// +unionDiscriminator\n176\t\t// +required\n177\t\tMode BootImageSkewEnforcementModeStatus `json:\"mode,omitempty\"`\n178\t\n179\t\t// automatic describes the current boot image of the cluster.\n180\t\t// This will be populated by the MCO when performing boot image updates. This value will be compared against\n181\t\t// the cluster's skew limit to determine skew compliance.\n182\t\t// Required when mode is set to \"Automatic\" and forbidden otherwise.\n183\t\t// +optional\n184\t\tAutomatic ClusterBootImageAutomatic `json:\"automatic,omitempty,omitzero\"`\n185\t\n186\t\t// manual describes the current boot image of the cluster.\n187\t\t// This will be populated by the MCO using the values provided in the spec.bootImageSkewEnforcement.manual field.\n188\t\t// This value will be compared against the cluster's skew limit to determine skew compliance.\n189\t\t// Required when mode is set to \"Manual\" and forbidden otherwise.\n190\t\t// +optional\n191\t\tManual ClusterBootImageManual `json:\"manual,omitempty,omitzero\"`\n192\t}\n193\t\n194\t// ClusterBootImageAutomatic is used to describe the cluster boot image in Automatic mode. It stores the RHCOS version of the\n195\t// boot image and the OCP release version which shipped with that RHCOS boot image. At least one of these values are required.\n196\t// If ocpVersion and rhcosVersion are defined, both values will be used for checking skew compliance.\n197\t// If only ocpVersion is defined, only that value will be used for checking skew compliance.\n198\t// If only rhcosVersion is defined, only that value will be used for checking skew compliance.\n199\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.ocpVersion) || has(self.rhcosVersion)\",message=\"at least one of ocpVersion or rhcosVersion is required\"\n200\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinProperties=1\n201\ttype ClusterBootImageAutomatic struct {\n202\t\t// ocpVersion provides a string which represents the OCP version of the boot image.\n203\t\t// This field must match the OCP semver compatible format of x.y.z. This field must be between\n204\t\t// 5 and 10 characters long.\n205\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.matches('^[0-9]+\\\\\\\\.[0-9]+\\\\\\\\.[0-9]+$')\",message=\"ocpVersion must match the OCP semver compatible format of x.y.z\"\n206\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxLength:=10\n207\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength:=5\n208\t\t// +optional\n209\t\tOCPVersion string `json:\"ocpVersion,omitempty\"`\n210\t\n211\t\t// rhcosVersion provides a string which represents the RHCOS version of the boot image\n212\t\t// This field must match rhcosVersion formatting of [major].[minor].[datestamp(YYYYMMDD)]-[buildnumber] or the legacy\n213\t\t// format of [major].[minor].[timestamp(YYYYMMDDHHmm)]-[buildnumber]. This field must be between\n214\t\t// 14 and 21 characters long.\n215\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.matches('^[0-9]+\\\\\\\\.[0-9]+\\\\\\\\.([0-9]{8}|[0-9]{12})-[0-9]+$')\",message=\"rhcosVersion must match format [major].[minor].[datestamp(YYYYMMDD)]-[buildnumber] or must match legacy format [major].[minor].[timestamp(YYYYMMDDHHmm)]-[buildnumber]\"\n216\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxLength:=21\n217\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength:=14\n218\t\t// +optional\n219\t\tRHCOSVersion string `json:\"rhcosVersion,omitempty\"`\n220\t}\n221\t\n222\t// BootImageSkewEnforcementConfigMode is a string enum used to configure the cluster's boot image skew enforcement mode.\n223\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum:=\"Manual\";\"None\"\n224\ttype BootImageSkewEnforcementConfigMode string\n225\t\n226\tconst (\n227\t\t// Manual represents a configuration mode that allows manual skew enforcement.\n228\t\tBootImageSkewEnforcementConfigModeManual BootImageSkewEnforcementConfigMode = \"Manual\"\n229\t\n230\t\t// None represents a configuration mode that disables boot image skew enforcement.\n231\t\tBootImageSkewEnforcementConfigModeNone BootImageSkewEnforcementConfigMode = \"None\"\n232\t)\n233\t\n234\t// BootImageSkewEnforcementModeStatus is a string enum used to indicate the cluster's boot image skew enforcement mode.\n235\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum:=\"Automatic\";\"Manual\";\"None\"\n236\ttype BootImageSkewEnforcementModeStatus string\n237\t\n238\tconst (\n239\t\t// Automatic represents a configuration mode that allows automatic skew enforcement.\n240\t\tBootImageSkewEnforcementModeStatusAutomatic BootImageSkewEnforcementModeStatus = \"Automatic\"\n241\t\n242\t\t// Manual represents a configuration mode that allows manual skew enforcement.\n243\t\tBootImageSkewEnforcementModeStatusManual BootImageSkewEnforcementModeStatus = \"Manual\"\n244\t\n245\t\t// None represents a configuration mode that disables boot image skew enforcement.\n246\t\tBootImageSkewEnforcementModeStatusNone BootImageSkewEnforcementModeStatus = \"None\"\n247\t)\n248\t\n249\ttype MachineConfigurationStatus struct {\n250\t\t// observedGeneration is the last generation change you've dealt with\n251\t\t// +optional\n252\t\tObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n253\t\n254\t\t// conditions is a list of conditions and their status\n255\t\t// +listType=map\n256\t\t// +listMapKey=type\n257\t\t// +optional\n258\t\tConditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n259\t\n260\t\t// Previously there was a StaticPodOperatorStatus here for legacy reasons. Many of the fields within\n261\t\t// it are no longer relevant for the MachineConfiguration CRD's functions. The following remainder\n262\t\t// fields were tombstoned after lifting out StaticPodOperatorStatus. To avoid conflicts with\n263\t\t// serialisation, the following field names may never be used again.\n264\t\n265\t\t// Tombstone: legacy field from StaticPodOperatorStatus\n266\t\t// Version string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n267\t\n268\t\t// Tombstone: legacy field from StaticPodOperatorStatus\n269\t\t// ReadyReplicas int32 `json:\"readyReplicas\"`\n270\t\n271\t\t// Tombstone: legacy field from StaticPodOperatorStatus\n272\t\t// Generations []GenerationStatus `json:\"generations,omitempty\"`\n273\t\n274\t\t// Tombstone: legacy field from StaticPodOperatorStatus\n275\t\t// LatestAvailableRevision int32 `json:\"latestAvailableRevision,omitempty\"`\n276\t\n277\t\t// Tombstone: legacy field from StaticPodOperatorStatus\n278\t\t// LatestAvailableRevisionReason string `json:\"latestAvailableRevisionReason,omitempty\"`\n279\t\n280\t\t// Tombstone: legacy field from StaticPodOperatorStatus\n281\t\t// NodeStatuses []NodeStatus `json:\"nodeStatuses,omitempty\"`\n282\t\n283\t\t// nodeDisruptionPolicyStatus status reflects what the latest cluster-validated policies are,\n284\t\t// and will be used by the Machine Config Daemon during future node updates.\n285\t\t// +optional\n286\t\tNodeDisruptionPolicyStatus NodeDisruptionPolicyStatus `json:\"nodeDisruptionPolicyStatus\"`\n287\t\n288\t\t// managedBootImagesStatus reflects what the latest cluster-validated boot image configuration is\n289\t\t// and will be used by Machine Config Controller while performing boot image updates.\n290\t\t// +optional\n291\t\tManagedBootImagesStatus ManagedBootImages `json:\"managedBootImagesStatus\"`\n292\t\n293\t\t// bootImageSkewEnforcementStatus reflects what the latest cluster-validated boot image skew enforcement\n294\t\t// configuration is and will be used by Machine Config Controller while performing boot image skew enforcement.\n295\t\t// When omitted, the MCO has no knowledge of how to enforce boot image skew. When the MCO does not know how\n296\t\t// boot image skew should be enforced, cluster upgrades will be blocked until it can either automatically\n297\t\t// determine skew enforcement or there is an explicit skew enforcement configuration provided in the\n298\t\t// spec.bootImageSkewEnforcement field.\n299\t\t// +openshift:enable:FeatureGate=BootImageSkewEnforcement\n300\t\t// +optional\n301\t\tBootImageSkewEnforcementStatus BootImageSkewEnforcementStatus `json:\"bootImageSkewEnforcementStatus,omitempty,omitzero\"`\n302\t}\n303\t\n304\t// +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n305\t\n306\t// MachineConfigurationList is a collection of items\n307\t//\n308\t// Compatibility level 1: Stable within a major release for a minimum of 12 months or 3 minor releases (whichever is longer).\n309\t// +openshift:compatibility-gen:level=1\n310\ttype MachineConfigurationList struct {\n311\t\tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n312\t\n313\t\t// metadata is the standard list's metadata.\n314\t\t// More info: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md#metadata\n315\t\tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata\"`\n316\t\n317\t\t// items contains the items\n318\t\tItems []MachineConfiguration `json:\"items\"`\n319\t}\n320\t\n321\t// IrreconcilableValidationOverridesStorage defines available storage irreconcilable overrides.\n322\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Disks;FileSystems;Raid\n323\ttype IrreconcilableValidationOverridesStorage string\n324\t\n325\tconst (\n326\t\t// Disks enables changes to the `spec.config.storage.disks` section of MachineConfig CRs.\n327\t\tIrreconcilableValidationOverridesStorageDisks IrreconcilableValidationOverridesStorage = \"Disks\"\n328\t\n329\t\t// FileSystems enables changes to the `spec.config.storage.filesystems` section of MachineConfig CRs.\n330\t\tIrreconcilableValidationOverridesStorageFileSystems IrreconcilableValidationOverridesStorage = \"FileSystems\"\n331\t\n332\t\t// Raid enables changes to the `spec.config.storage.raid` section of MachineConfig CRs.\n333\t\tIrreconcilableValidationOverridesStorageRaid IrreconcilableValidationOverridesStorage = \"Raid\"\n334\t)\n335\t\n336\t// IrreconcilableValidationOverrides holds the irreconcilable validations overrides to be applied on each rendered\n337\t// MachineConfig generation.\n338\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinProperties=1\n339\ttype IrreconcilableValidationOverrides struct {\n340\t\t// storage can be used to allow making irreconcilable changes to the selected sections under the\n341\t\t// `spec.config.storage` field of MachineConfig CRs\n342\t\t// It must have at least one item, may not exceed 3 items and must not contain duplicates.\n343\t\t// Allowed element values are \"Disks\", \"FileSystems\", \"Raid\" and omitted.\n344\t\t// When contains \"Disks\" changes to the `spec.config.storage.disks` section of MachineConfig CRs are allowed.\n345\t\t// When contains \"FileSystems\" changes to the `spec.config.storage.filesystems` section of MachineConfig CRs are allowed.\n346\t\t// When contains \"Raid\" changes to the `spec.config.storage.raid` section of MachineConfig CRs are allowed.\n347\t\t// When omitted changes to the `spec.config.storage` section are forbidden.\n348\t\t// +optional\n349\t\t// +listType=set\n350\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinItems=1\n351\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=3\n352\t\tStorage []IrreconcilableValidationOverridesStorage `json:\"storage,omitempty,omitzero\"`\n353\t}\n354\t\n355\ttype ManagedBootImages struct {\n356\t\t// machineManagers can be used to register machine management resources for boot image updates. The Machine Config Operator\n357\t\t// will watch for changes to this list. Only one entry is permitted per type of machine management resource.\n358\t\t// +optional\n359\t\t// +listType=map\n360\t\t// +listMapKey=resource\n361\t\t// +listMapKey=apiGroup\n362\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=5\n363\t\tMachineManagers []MachineManager `json:\"machineManagers\"`\n364\t}\n365\t\n366\t// MachineManager describes a target machine resource that is registered for boot image updates. It stores identifying information\n367\t// such as the resource type and the API Group of the resource. It also provides granular control via the selection field.\n368\t// +openshift:validation:FeatureGateAwareXValidation:requiredFeatureGate=ManagedBootImagesCPMS,rule=\"self.resource != 'controlplanemachinesets' || self.selection.mode == 'All' || self.selection.mode == 'None'\", message=\"Only All or None selection mode is permitted for ControlPlaneMachineSets\"\n369\ttype MachineManager struct {\n370\t\t// resource is the machine management resource's type.\n371\t\t// Valid values are machinesets and controlplanemachinesets.\n372\t\t// machinesets means that the machine manager will only register resources of the kind MachineSet.\n373\t\t// controlplanemachinesets means that the machine manager will only register resources of the kind ControlPlaneMachineSet.\n374\t\t// +required\n375\t\tResource MachineManagerMachineSetsResourceType `json:\"resource\"`\n376\t\n377\t\t// apiGroup is name of the APIGroup that the machine management resource belongs to.\n378\t\t// The only current valid value is machine.openshift.io.\n379\t\t// machine.openshift.io means that the machine manager will only register resources that belong to OpenShift machine API group.\n380\t\t// +required\n381\t\tAPIGroup MachineManagerMachineSetsAPIGroupType `json:\"apiGroup\"`\n382\t\n383\t\t// selection allows granular control of the machine management resources that will be registered for boot image updates.\n384\t\t// +required\n385\t\tSelection MachineManagerSelector `json:\"selection\"`\n386\t}\n387\t\n388\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.mode) && self.mode == 'Partial' ?  has(self.partial) : !has(self.partial)\",message=\"Partial is required when type is partial, and forbidden otherwise\"\n389\t// +union\n390\ttype MachineManagerSelector struct {\n391\t\t// mode determines how machine managers will be selected for updates.\n392\t\t// Valid values are All, Partial and None.\n393\t\t// All means that every resource matched by the machine manager will be updated.\n394\t\t// Partial requires specified selector(s) and allows customisation of which resources matched by the machine manager will be updated.\n395\t\t// Partial is not permitted for the controlplanemachinesets resource type as they are a singleton within the cluster.\n396\t\t// None means that every resource matched by the machine manager will not be updated.\n397\t\t// +unionDiscriminator\n398\t\t// +required\n399\t\tMode MachineManagerSelectorMode `json:\"mode\"`\n400\t\n401\t\t// partial provides label selector(s) that can be used to match machine management resources.\n402\t\t// Only permitted when mode is set to \"Partial\".\n403\t\t// +optional\n404\t\tPartial *PartialSelector `json:\"partial,omitempty\"`\n405\t}\n406\t\n407\t// PartialSelector provides label selector(s) that can be used to match machine management resources.\n408\ttype PartialSelector struct {\n409\t\t// machineResourceSelector is a label selector that can be used to select machine resources like MachineSets.\n410\t\t// +required\n411\t\tMachineResourceSelector *metav1.LabelSelector `json:\"machineResourceSelector,omitempty\"`\n412\t}\n413\t\n414\t// MachineManagerSelectorMode is a string enum used in the MachineManagerSelector union discriminator.\n415\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum:=\"All\";\"Partial\";\"None\"\n416\ttype MachineManagerSelectorMode string\n417\t\n418\tconst (\n419\t\t// All represents a configuration mode that registers all resources specified by the parent MachineManager for boot image updates.\n420\t\tAll MachineManagerSelectorMode = \"All\"\n421\t\n422\t\t// Partial represents a configuration mode that will register resources specified by the parent MachineManager only\n423\t\t// if they match with the label selector.\n424\t\tPartial MachineManagerSelectorMode = \"Partial\"\n425\t\n426\t\t// None represents a configuration mode that excludes all resources specified by the parent MachineManager from boot image updates.\n427\t\tNone MachineManagerSelectorMode = \"None\"\n428\t)\n429\t\n430\t// MachineManagerManagedResourceType is a string enum used in the MachineManager type to describe the resource\n431\t// type to be registered.\n432\t// +openshift:validation:FeatureGateAwareEnum:featureGate=\"\",enum=machinesets\n433\t// +openshift:validation:FeatureGateAwareEnum:featureGate=ManagedBootImagesCPMS,enum=machinesets;controlplanemachinesets\n434\ttype MachineManagerMachineSetsResourceType string\n435\t\n436\tconst (\n437\t\t// MachineSets represent the MachineSet resource type, which manage a group of machines and belong to the Openshift machine API group.\n438\t\tMachineSets MachineManagerMachineSetsResourceType = \"machinesets\"\n439\t\t// ControlPlaneMachineSets represent the ControlPlaneMachineSets resource type, which manage a group of control-plane machines and belong to the Openshift machine API group.\n440\t\tControlPlaneMachineSets MachineManagerMachineSetsResourceType = \"controlplanemachinesets\"\n441\t)\n442\t\n443\t// MachineManagerManagedAPIGroupType is a string enum used in in the MachineManager type to describe the APIGroup\n444\t// of the resource type being registered.\n445\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum:=\"machine.openshift.io\"\n446\ttype MachineManagerMachineSetsAPIGroupType string\n447\t\n448\tconst (\n449\t\t// MachineAPI represent the traditional MAPI Group that a machineset may belong to.\n450\t\t// This feature only supports MAPI machinesets and controlplanemachinesets at this time.\n451\t\tMachineAPI MachineManagerMachineSetsAPIGroupType = \"machine.openshift.io\"\n452\t)\n453\t\n454\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicyStatus struct {\n455\t\t// clusterPolicies is a merge of cluster default and user provided node disruption policies.\n456\t\t// +optional\n457\t\tClusterPolicies NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus `json:\"clusterPolicies\"`\n458\t}\n459\t\n460\t// NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig is the overall spec definition for files/units/sshkeys\n461\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig struct {\n462\t\t// files is a list of MachineConfig file definitions and actions to take to changes on those paths\n463\t\t// This list supports a maximum of 50 entries.\n464\t\t// +optional\n465\t\t// +listType=map\n466\t\t// +listMapKey=path\n467\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=50\n468\t\tFiles []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecFile `json:\"files\"`\n469\t\t// units is a list MachineConfig unit definitions and actions to take on changes to those services\n470\t\t// This list supports a maximum of 50 entries.\n471\t\t// +optional\n472\t\t// +listType=map\n473\t\t// +listMapKey=name\n474\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=50\n475\t\tUnits []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecUnit `json:\"units\"`\n476\t\t// sshkey maps to the ignition.sshkeys field in the MachineConfig object, definition an action for this\n477\t\t// will apply to all sshkey changes in the cluster\n478\t\t// +optional\n479\t\tSSHKey NodeDisruptionPolicySpecSSHKey `json:\"sshkey\"`\n480\t}\n481\t\n482\t// NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus is the type for the status object, rendered by the controller as a\n483\t// merge of cluster defaults and user provided policies\n484\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus struct {\n485\t\t// files is a list of MachineConfig file definitions and actions to take to changes on those paths\n486\t\t// +optional\n487\t\t// +listType=map\n488\t\t// +listMapKey=path\n489\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=100\n490\t\tFiles []NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusFile `json:\"files,omitempty\"`\n491\t\t// units is a list MachineConfig unit definitions and actions to take on changes to those services\n492\t\t// +optional\n493\t\t// +listType=map\n494\t\t// +listMapKey=name\n495\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=100\n496\t\tUnits []NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusUnit `json:\"units,omitempty\"`\n497\t\t// sshkey is the overall sshkey MachineConfig definition\n498\t\t// +optional\n499\t\tSSHKey NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusSSHKey `json:\"sshkey,omitempty\"`\n500\t}\n501\t\n502\t// NodeDisruptionPolicySpecFile is a file entry and corresponding actions to take and is used in the NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig object\n503\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecFile struct {\n504\t\t// path is the location of a file being managed through a MachineConfig.\n505\t\t// The Actions in the policy will apply to changes to the file at this path.\n506\t\t// +required\n507\t\tPath string `json:\"path\"`\n508\t\t// actions represents the series of commands to be executed on changes to the file at\n509\t\t// the corresponding file path. Actions will be applied in the order that\n510\t\t// they are set in this list. If there are other incoming changes to other MachineConfig\n511\t\t// entries in the same update that require a reboot, the reboot will supercede these actions.\n512\t\t// Valid actions are Reboot, Drain, Reload, DaemonReload and None.\n513\t\t// The Reboot action and the None action cannot be used in conjunction with any of the other actions.\n514\t\t// This list supports a maximum of 10 entries.\n515\t\t// +required\n516\t\t// +listType=atomic\n517\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=10\n518\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='Reboot') ? size(self) == 1 : true\", message=\"Reboot action can only be specified standalone, as it will override any other actions\"\n519\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='None') ? size(self) == 1 : true\", message=\"None action can only be specified standalone, as it will override any other actions\"\n520\t\tActions []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction `json:\"actions\"`\n521\t}\n522\t\n523\t// NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusFile is a file entry and corresponding actions to take and is used in the NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus object\n524\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusFile struct {\n525\t\t// path is the location of a file being managed through a MachineConfig.\n526\t\t// The Actions in the policy will apply to changes to the file at this path.\n527\t\t// +required\n528\t\tPath string `json:\"path\"`\n529\t\t// actions represents the series of commands to be executed on changes to the file at\n530\t\t// the corresponding file path. Actions will be applied in the order that\n531\t\t// they are set in this list. If there are other incoming changes to other MachineConfig\n532\t\t// entries in the same update that require a reboot, the reboot will supercede these actions.\n533\t\t// Valid actions are Reboot, Drain, Reload, DaemonReload and None.\n534\t\t// The Reboot action and the None action cannot be used in conjunction with any of the other actions.\n535\t\t// This list supports a maximum of 10 entries.\n536\t\t// +required\n537\t\t// +listType=atomic\n538\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=10\n539\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='Reboot') ? size(self) == 1 : true\", message=\"Reboot action can only be specified standalone, as it will override any other actions\"\n540\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='None') ? size(self) == 1 : true\", message=\"None action can only be specified standalone, as it will override any other actions\"\n541\t\tActions []NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusAction `json:\"actions\"`\n542\t}\n543\t\n544\t// NodeDisruptionPolicySpecUnit is a systemd unit name and corresponding actions to take and is used in the NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig object\n545\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecUnit struct {\n546\t\t// name represents the service name of a systemd service managed through a MachineConfig\n547\t\t// Actions specified will be applied for changes to the named service.\n548\t\t// Service names should be of the format ${NAME}${SERVICETYPE} and can up to 255 characters long.\n549\t\t// ${NAME} must be atleast 1 character long and can only consist of alphabets, digits, \":\", \"-\", \"_\", \".\", and \"\\\".\n550\t\t// ${SERVICETYPE} must be one of \".service\", \".socket\", \".device\", \".mount\", \".automount\", \".swap\", \".target\", \".path\", \".timer\", \".snapshot\", \".slice\" or \".scope\".\n551\t\t// +required\n552\t\tName NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName `json:\"name\"`\n553\t\n554\t\t// actions represents the series of commands to be executed on changes to the file at\n555\t\t// the corresponding file path. Actions will be applied in the order that\n556\t\t// they are set in this list. If there are other incoming changes to other MachineConfig\n557\t\t// entries in the same update that require a reboot, the reboot will supercede these actions.\n558\t\t// Valid actions are Reboot, Drain, Reload, DaemonReload and None.\n559\t\t// The Reboot action and the None action cannot be used in conjunction with any of the other actions.\n560\t\t// This list supports a maximum of 10 entries.\n561\t\t// +required\n562\t\t// +listType=atomic\n563\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=10\n564\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='Reboot') ? size(self) == 1 : true\", message=\"Reboot action can only be specified standalone, as it will override any other actions\"\n565\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='None') ? size(self) == 1 : true\", message=\"None action can only be specified standalone, as it will override any other actions\"\n566\t\tActions []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction `json:\"actions\"`\n567\t}\n568\t\n569\t// NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusUnit is a systemd unit name and corresponding actions to take and is used in the NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus object\n570\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusUnit struct {\n571\t\t// name represents the service name of a systemd service managed through a MachineConfig\n572\t\t// Actions specified will be applied for changes to the named service.\n573\t\t// Service names should be of the format ${NAME}${SERVICETYPE} and can up to 255 characters long.\n574\t\t// ${NAME} must be atleast 1 character long and can only consist of alphabets, digits, \":\", \"-\", \"_\", \".\", and \"\\\".\n575\t\t// ${SERVICETYPE} must be one of \".service\", \".socket\", \".device\", \".mount\", \".automount\", \".swap\", \".target\", \".path\", \".timer\", \".snapshot\", \".slice\" or \".scope\".\n576\t\t// +required\n577\t\tName NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName `json:\"name\"`\n578\t\n579\t\t// actions represents the series of commands to be executed on changes to the file at\n580\t\t// the corresponding file path. Actions will be applied in the order that\n581\t\t// they are set in this list. If there are other incoming changes to other MachineConfig\n582\t\t// entries in the same update that require a reboot, the reboot will supercede these actions.\n583\t\t// Valid actions are Reboot, Drain, Reload, DaemonReload and None.\n584\t\t// The Reboot action and the None action cannot be used in conjunction with any of the other actions.\n585\t\t// This list supports a maximum of 10 entries.\n586\t\t// +required\n587\t\t// +listType=atomic\n588\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=10\n589\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='Reboot') ? size(self) == 1 : true\", message=\"Reboot action can only be specified standalone, as it will override any other actions\"\n590\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='None') ? size(self) == 1 : true\", message=\"None action can only be specified standalone, as it will override any other actions\"\n591\t\tActions []NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusAction `json:\"actions\"`\n592\t}\n593\t\n594\t// NodeDisruptionPolicySpecSSHKey is actions to take for any SSHKey change and is used in the NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig object\n595\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecSSHKey struct {\n596\t\t// actions represents the series of commands to be executed on changes to the file at\n597\t\t// the corresponding file path. Actions will be applied in the order that\n598\t\t// they are set in this list. If there are other incoming changes to other MachineConfig\n599\t\t// entries in the same update that require a reboot, the reboot will supercede these actions.\n600\t\t// Valid actions are Reboot, Drain, Reload, DaemonReload and None.\n601\t\t// The Reboot action and the None action cannot be used in conjunction with any of the other actions.\n602\t\t// This list supports a maximum of 10 entries.\n603\t\t// +required\n604\t\t// +listType=atomic\n605\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=10\n606\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='Reboot') ? size(self) == 1 : true\", message=\"Reboot action can only be specified standalone, as it will override any other actions\"\n607\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='None') ? size(self) == 1 : true\", message=\"None action can only be specified standalone, as it will override any other actions\"\n608\t\tActions []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction `json:\"actions\"`\n609\t}\n610\t\n611\t// NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusSSHKey is actions to take for any SSHKey change and is used in the NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus object\n612\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusSSHKey struct {\n613\t\t// actions represents the series of commands to be executed on changes to the file at\n614\t\t// the corresponding file path. Actions will be applied in the order that\n615\t\t// they are set in this list. If there are other incoming changes to other MachineConfig\n616\t\t// entries in the same update that require a reboot, the reboot will supercede these actions.\n617\t\t// Valid actions are Reboot, Drain, Reload, DaemonReload and None.\n618\t\t// The Reboot action and the None action cannot be used in conjunction with any of the other actions.\n619\t\t// This list supports a maximum of 10 entries.\n620\t\t// +required\n621\t\t// +listType=atomic\n622\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=10\n623\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='Reboot') ? size(self) == 1 : true\", message=\"Reboot action can only be specified standalone, as it will override any other actions\"\n624\t\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='None') ? size(self) == 1 : true\", message=\"None action can only be specified standalone, as it will override any other actions\"\n625\t\tActions []NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusAction `json:\"actions\"`\n626\t}\n627\t\n628\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.type) && self.type == 'Reload' ? has(self.reload) : !has(self.reload)\",message=\"reload is required when type is Reload, and forbidden otherwise\"\n629\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.type) && self.type == 'Restart' ? has(self.restart) : !has(self.restart)\",message=\"restart is required when type is Restart, and forbidden otherwise\"\n630\t// +union\n631\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction struct {\n632\t\t// type represents the commands that will be carried out if this NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType is executed\n633\t\t// Valid values are Reboot, Drain, Reload, Restart, DaemonReload and None.\n634\t\t// reload/restart requires a corresponding service target specified in the reload/restart field.\n635\t\t// Other values require no further configuration\n636\t\t// +unionDiscriminator\n637\t\t// +required\n638\t\tType NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType `json:\"type\"`\n639\t\t// reload specifies the service to reload, only valid if type is reload\n640\t\t// +optional\n641\t\tReload *ReloadService `json:\"reload,omitempty\"`\n642\t\t// restart specifies the service to restart, only valid if type is restart\n643\t\t// +optional\n644\t\tRestart *RestartService `json:\"restart,omitempty\"`\n645\t}\n646\t\n647\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.type) && self.type == 'Reload' ? has(self.reload) : !has(self.reload)\",message=\"reload is required when type is Reload, and forbidden otherwise\"\n648\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.type) && self.type == 'Restart' ? has(self.restart) : !has(self.restart)\",message=\"restart is required when type is Restart, and forbidden otherwise\"\n649\t// +union\n650\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusAction struct {\n651\t\t// type represents the commands that will be carried out if this NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType is executed\n652\t\t// Valid values are Reboot, Drain, Reload, Restart, DaemonReload, None and Special.\n653\t\t// reload/restart requires a corresponding service target specified in the reload/restart field.\n654\t\t// Other values require no further configuration\n655\t\t// +unionDiscriminator\n656\t\t// +required\n657\t\tType NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType `json:\"type\"`\n658\t\t// reload specifies the service to reload, only valid if type is reload\n659\t\t// +optional\n660\t\tReload *ReloadService `json:\"reload,omitempty\"`\n661\t\t// restart specifies the service to restart, only valid if type is restart\n662\t\t// +optional\n663\t\tRestart *RestartService `json:\"restart,omitempty\"`\n664\t}\n665\t\n666\t// ReloadService allows the user to specify the services to be reloaded\n667\ttype ReloadService struct {\n668\t\t// serviceName is the full name (e.g. crio.service) of the service to be reloaded\n669\t\t// Service names should be of the format ${NAME}${SERVICETYPE} and can up to 255 characters long.\n670\t\t// ${NAME} must be atleast 1 character long and can only consist of alphabets, digits, \":\", \"-\", \"_\", \".\", and \"\\\".\n671\t\t// ${SERVICETYPE} must be one of \".service\", \".socket\", \".device\", \".mount\", \".automount\", \".swap\", \".target\", \".path\", \".timer\", \".snapshot\", \".slice\" or \".scope\".\n672\t\t// +required\n673\t\tServiceName NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName `json:\"serviceName\"`\n674\t}\n675\t\n676\t// RestartService allows the user to specify the services to be restarted\n677\ttype RestartService struct {\n678\t\t// serviceName is the full name (e.g. crio.service) of the service to be restarted\n679\t\t// Service names should be of the format ${NAME}${SERVICETYPE} and can up to 255 characters long.\n680\t\t// ${NAME} must be atleast 1 character long and can only consist of alphabets, digits, \":\", \"-\", \"_\", \".\", and \"\\\".\n681\t\t// ${SERVICETYPE} must be one of \".service\", \".socket\", \".device\", \".mount\", \".automount\", \".swap\", \".target\", \".path\", \".timer\", \".snapshot\", \".slice\" or \".scope\".\n682\t\t// +required\n683\t\tServiceName NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName `json:\"serviceName\"`\n684\t}\n685\t\n686\t// NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType is a string enum used in a NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction object. They describe an action to be performed.\n687\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum:=\"Reboot\";\"Drain\";\"Reload\";\"Restart\";\"DaemonReload\";\"None\"\n688\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType string\n689\t\n690\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=`self.matches('\\\\.(service|socket|device|mount|automount|swap|target|path|timer|snapshot|slice|scope)$')`, message=\"Invalid ${SERVICETYPE} in service name. Expected format is ${NAME}${SERVICETYPE}, where ${SERVICETYPE} must be one of \\\".service\\\", \\\".socket\\\", \\\".device\\\", \\\".mount\\\", \\\".automount\\\", \\\".swap\\\", \\\".target\\\", \\\".path\\\", \\\".timer\\\",\\\".snapshot\\\", \\\".slice\\\" or \\\".scope\\\".\"\n691\t// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=`self.matches('^[a-zA-Z0-9:._\\\\\\\\-]+\\\\..')`, message=\"Invalid ${NAME} in service name. Expected format is ${NAME}${SERVICETYPE}, where {NAME} must be atleast 1 character long and can only consist of alphabets, digits, \\\":\\\", \\\"-\\\", \\\"_\\\", \\\".\\\", and \\\"\\\\\\\"\"\n692\t// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxLength=255\n693\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName string\n694\t\n695\tconst (\n696\t\t// Reboot represents an action that will cause nodes to be rebooted. This is the default action by the MCO\n697\t\t// if a reboot policy is not found for a change/update being performed by the MCO.\n698\t\tRebootSpecAction NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"Reboot\"\n699\t\n700\t\t// Drain represents an action that will cause nodes to be drained of their workloads.\n701\t\tDrainSpecAction NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"Drain\"\n702\t\n703\t\t// Reload represents an action that will cause nodes to reload the service described by the Target field.\n704\t\tReloadSpecAction NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"Reload\"\n705\t\n706\t\t// Restart represents an action that will cause nodes to restart the service described by the Target field.\n707\t\tRestartSpecAction NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"Restart\"\n708\t\n709\t\t// DaemonReload represents an action that TBD\n710\t\tDaemonReloadSpecAction NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"DaemonReload\"\n711\t\n712\t\t// None represents an action that no handling is required by the MCO.\n713\t\tNoneSpecAction NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"None\"\n714\t)\n715\t\n716\t// NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType is a string enum used in a NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusAction object. They describe an action to be performed.\n717\t// The key difference of this object from NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType is that there is a additional SpecialStatusAction value in this enum. This will only be\n718\t// used by the MCO's controller to indicate some internal actions. They are not part of the NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig object and cannot be set by the user.\n719\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum:=\"Reboot\";\"Drain\";\"Reload\";\"Restart\";\"DaemonReload\";\"None\";\"Special\"\n720\ttype NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType string\n721\t\n722\tconst (\n723\t\t// Reboot represents an action that will cause nodes to be rebooted. This is the default action by the MCO\n724\t\t// if a reboot policy is not found for a change/update being performed by the MCO.\n725\t\tRebootStatusAction NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType = \"Reboot\"\n726\t\n727\t\t// Drain represents an action that will cause nodes to be drained of their workloads.\n728\t\tDrainStatusAction NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType = \"Drain\"\n729\t\n730\t\t// Reload represents an action that will cause nodes to reload the service described by the Target field.\n731\t\tReloadStatusAction NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType = \"Reload\"\n732\t\n733\t\t// Restart represents an action that will cause nodes to restart the service described by the Target field.\n734\t\tRestartStatusAction NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType = \"Restart\"\n735\t\n736\t\t// DaemonReload represents an action that TBD\n737\t\tDaemonReloadStatusAction NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType = \"DaemonReload\"\n738\t\n739\t\t// None represents an action that no handling is required by the MCO.\n740\t\tNoneStatusAction NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType = \"None\"\n741\t\n742\t\t// Special represents an action that is internal to the MCO, and is not allowed in user defined NodeDisruption policies.\n743\t\tSpecialStatusAction NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType = \"Special\"\n744\t)\n745\t\n746\t// These strings will be used for MachineConfiguration Status conditions.\n747\tconst (\n748\t\t// MachineConfigurationBootImageUpdateDegraded means that the MCO ran into an error while reconciling boot images. This\n749\t\t// will cause the clusteroperators.config.openshift.io/machine-config to degrade. This  condition will indicate the cause\n750\t\t// of the degrade, the progress of the update and the generation of the boot images configmap that it degraded on.\n751\t\tMachineConfigurationBootImageUpdateDegraded string = \"BootImageUpdateDegraded\"\n752\t\n753\t\t// MachineConfigurationBootImageUpdateProgressing means that the MCO is in the process of reconciling boot images. This\n754\t\t// will cause the clusteroperators.config.openshift.io/machine-config to be in a Progressing state. This condition will\n755\t\t// indicate the progress of the update and the generation of the boot images configmap that triggered this update.\n756\t\tMachineConfigurationBootImageUpdateProgressing string = \"BootImageUpdateProgressing\"\n757\t)\n758\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_012eYNRCZfJyWnRLE9EjXoPk","session_id":"1ca7e20c-f463-4aff-8411-4663c8d63aa4","uuid":"b0a0b50f-28fb-45d9-9640-90f390148bbe","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:23:45.822Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Find NodeDisruptionPolicy API types and examples"}
