{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_012eYNRCZfJyWnRLE9EjXoPk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a comprehensive picture. Here is the complete findings report.\n\n---\n\n## NodeDisruptionPolicy Type Definitions, Examples, and Validation Logic\n\n### 1. Primary Type Definitions\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/operator/v1/types_machineconfiguration.go`\n\nAll types live in the `operator/v1` package (`opv1` alias throughout the codebase).\n\n#### Top-level anchor on `MachineConfigurationSpec` (line 58)\n```go\nNodeDisruptionPolicy NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig `json:\"nodeDisruptionPolicy\"`\n```\nComment: \"allows an admin to set granular node disruption actions for MachineConfig-based updates, such as drains, service reloads, etc. Specifying this will allow for less downtime when doing small configuration updates to the cluster. This configuration has no effect on cluster upgrades which will still incur node disruption where required.\"\n\n#### Top-level anchor on `MachineConfigurationStatus` (line 286)\n```go\nNodeDisruptionPolicyStatus NodeDisruptionPolicyStatus `json:\"nodeDisruptionPolicyStatus\"`\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig` (spec input, lines 461-480)\n```go\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig struct {\n    // files: list of MachineConfig file definitions and actions. Max 50 entries.\n    // +listType=map, +listMapKey=path, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=50\n    Files []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecFile `json:\"files\"`\n\n    // units: list of MachineConfig unit definitions and actions. Max 50 entries.\n    // +listType=map, +listMapKey=name, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=50\n    Units []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecUnit `json:\"units\"`\n\n    // sshkey: actions for all sshkey changes in the cluster\n    SSHKey NodeDisruptionPolicySpecSSHKey `json:\"sshkey\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatus` (lines 454-458)\n```go\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicyStatus struct {\n    // clusterPolicies: merge of cluster default and user provided policies\n    ClusterPolicies NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus `json:\"clusterPolicies\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus` (lines 484-500)\n```go\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus struct {\n    // +listType=map, +listMapKey=path, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=100\n    Files  []NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusFile  `json:\"files,omitempty\"`\n    // +listType=map, +listMapKey=name, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=100\n    Units  []NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusUnit  `json:\"units,omitempty\"`\n    SSHKey NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusSSHKey  `json:\"sshkey,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicySpecFile` (lines 503-521)\n```go\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecFile struct {\n    // path: location of a managed file. Actions apply to changes at this path.\n    // +required\n    Path string `json:\"path\"`\n\n    // actions: series of commands on file changes. Applied in list order.\n    // Reboot and None cannot be combined with other actions.\n    // Max 10 entries.\n    // +required, +listType=atomic, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=10\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='Reboot') ? size(self) == 1 : true\"\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='None') ? size(self) == 1 : true\"\n    Actions []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction `json:\"actions\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusFile` (lines 524-542) is structurally identical but uses `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusAction` instead, for the status side.\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicySpecUnit` (lines 544-567)\n```go\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecUnit struct {\n    // name: systemd service name. Format: ${NAME}${SERVICETYPE}, max 255 chars.\n    // ${SERVICETYPE} must be one of: .service .socket .device .mount .automount .swap\n    //   .target .path .timer .snapshot .slice .scope\n    // +required\n    Name NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName `json:\"name\"`\n\n    // actions: same rules as for files (Reboot/None standalone, max 10)\n    // +required, +listType=atomic, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=10\n    Actions []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction `json:\"actions\"`\n}\n```\n\nAgain a parallel `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusUnit` exists for the status side.\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicySpecSSHKey` / `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusSSHKey` (lines 594-626)\n```go\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecSSHKey struct {\n    // actions: same rules as files (Reboot/None standalone, max 10)\n    // +required, +listType=atomic, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=10\n    Actions []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction `json:\"actions\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction` â€” the union discriminator (lines 628-645)\n```go\n// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.type) && self.type == 'Reload' ? has(self.reload) : !has(self.reload)\"\n// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.type) && self.type == 'Restart' ? has(self.restart) : !has(self.restart)\"\n// +union\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction struct {\n    // type: Reboot | Drain | Reload | Restart | DaemonReload | None\n    // Reload/Restart require a corresponding reload/restart field.\n    // +unionDiscriminator, +required\n    Type NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType `json:\"type\"`\n\n    // reload: service to reload. Only valid when type==Reload.\n    // +optional\n    Reload  *ReloadService  `json:\"reload,omitempty\"`\n\n    // restart: service to restart. Only valid when type==Restart.\n    // +optional\n    Restart *RestartService `json:\"restart,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe status-side `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusAction` (lines 647-664) is the same shape but its `type` enum also includes `\"Special\"` (internal MCO action not user-settable).\n\n#### `ReloadService` / `RestartService` (lines 667-684)\n```go\ntype ReloadService struct {\n    // serviceName: full name e.g. crio.service. Same format/length rules as NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName.\n    // +required\n    ServiceName NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName `json:\"serviceName\"`\n}\n\ntype RestartService struct {\n    ServiceName NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName `json:\"serviceName\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName` â€” validated string type (lines 690-693)\n```go\n// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=`self.matches('\\\\.(service|socket|device|mount|automount|swap|target|path|timer|snapshot|slice|scope)$')`\n// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=`self.matches('^[a-zA-Z0-9:._\\\\\\\\-]+\\\\..')`\n// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxLength=255\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName string\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType` â€” enum (lines 687-688, 695-714)\n```go\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum:=\"Reboot\";\"Drain\";\"Reload\";\"Restart\";\"DaemonReload\";\"None\"\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType string\n\nconst (\n    RebootSpecAction      NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"Reboot\"\n    DrainSpecAction       NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"Drain\"\n    ReloadSpecAction      NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"Reload\"\n    RestartSpecAction     NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"Restart\"\n    DaemonReloadSpecAction NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"DaemonReload\"\n    NoneSpecAction        NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"None\"\n)\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType` â€” enum (lines 719-744)\nAdds `\"Special\"` to the above set. `Special` is internal-only; users cannot set it.\n\n---\n\n### 2. YAML Example / Test Fixture\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/machineconfigurations/nodedisruptionpolicy-rebootless-path.yaml`\n\nThis is an `openshift.io/v1 Template` that produces a `MachineConfiguration`:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: template.openshift.io/v1\nkind: Template\nmetadata:\n  name: node-disruption-policy\nobjects:\n- apiVersion: operator.openshift.io/v1\n  kind: MachineConfiguration\n  metadata:\n    name: cluster\n    namespace: openshift-machine-config-operator\n  spec:\n    nodeDisruptionPolicy:\n      files:\n        - path: /home/core/test\n          actions:\n            - type: None\n```\n\nThis is the only standalone YAML file in the repository. The e2e and extended-priv tests programmatically construct `NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig` objects using the server-side apply configuration builder (`mcoac.*`) rather than static YAML.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Validation Logic\n\n#### CEL / kubebuilder validation (compile-time, in API types)\n\nAll constraints are in the type definitions above. The key rules are:\n\n- `Reboot` and `None` actions are **standalone-only** â€” CEL rules on every `Actions` field:\n  - `self.exists(x, x.type=='Reboot') ? size(self) == 1 : true`\n  - `self.exists(x, x.type=='None') ? size(self) == 1 : true`\n- `Reload` requires a `reload` sub-field; `Restart` requires a `restart` sub-field (XValidation union discriminator rules on `NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction`).\n- `Files` and `Units` lists cap at **50 entries** in spec, **100** in status.\n- Each `Actions` list caps at **10 entries**.\n- `NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName` is validated to match the systemd service name format (regex + MaxLength=255).\n\n#### Controller defaulting / merge logic (runtime, in MCO operator)\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/apihelpers/apihelpers.go`\n\n`MergeClusterPolicies(userDefinedClusterPolicies NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig) NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus` (line 449) is the core merge function called from `pkg/operator/sync.go` line 2373 during every `syncMachineConfiguration` reconcile cycle:\n\n- Starts from hardcoded **default cluster policies** (`defaultClusterPolicies`, lines 24-194).\n- User-defined file/unit policies that **conflict** with defaults replace the default entry; otherwise they are appended.\n- If the user provides no SSH key actions, the default SSH policy is used (`NoneStatusAction`).\n- Result is stored in `MachineConfigurationStatus.NodeDisruptionPolicyStatus.ClusterPolicies`.\n\n**Default policies built into the MCO** (constants resolved from `pkg/daemon/constants/constants.go`):\n\n| Path / Unit | Default Action |\n|---|---|\n| `/var/lib/kubelet/config.json` | `None` |\n| `/etc/machine-config-daemon/no-reboot/containers-gpg.pub` | `Reload crio.service` |\n| `/etc/containers/policy.json` | `Reload crio.service` |\n| `/etc/containers/registries.conf` | `Special` (internal â€” triggers safe-merge check) |\n| `/etc/containers/registries.d` | `Reload crio.service` |\n| `/etc/crio/policies` | `Reload crio.service` |\n| `/etc/nmstate/openshift` | `None` |\n| `/etc/pki/ca-trust/source/anchors/openshift-config-user-ca-bundle.crt` | `Restart coreos-update-ca-trust.service`, then `Restart crio.service` |\n| `/etc/kubernetes/credential-providers` | `Restart kubelet.service` |\n| `/etc/systemd/system/kubelet.service.d/40-kubelet-crio-image-credential-provider.conf` | `DaemonReload`, then `Restart kubelet.service` |\n| `/etc/iri-registry` | `Restart iri-registry.service` |\n| `/usr/local/bin/load-registry-image.sh` | `Restart iri-registry.service` |\n| `/etc/pki/ca-trust/source/anchors/iri-root-ca.crt` | `Restart coreos-update-ca-trust.service` |\n| Unit `iri-registry.service` | `DaemonReload`, then `Restart iri-registry.service` |\n| SSHKey | `None` |\n\n#### Daemon action dispatch (runtime, in MCD)\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/daemon/update.go`\n\n- `calculatePostConfigChangeNodeDisruptionAction` (line 750) â€” polls until `MachineConfiguration/cluster` status is current (Generation == ObservedGeneration), then calls `calculatePostConfigChangeNodeDisruptionActionFromMCDiffs`.\n- `calculatePostConfigChangeNodeDisruptionActionFromMCDiffs` (line 655) â€” walks diff file paths using `FindClosestFilePolicyPathMatch` (longest-prefix directory match), walks diff units by exact name match, and appends SSH policy if SSH diff detected. Post-process rules: if any `Reboot` action appears, collapse to a single `Reboot`; strip redundant `None` actions when other actions are present.\n- `performPostConfigChangeNodeDisruptionAction` (line 165) â€” executes the resolved action list: Drain (no-op here, done earlier), Reboot, None (skip-reboot event), Restart, Reload, DaemonReload, Special (CRI-O reload).\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/daemon/drain.go`\n\n- `isDrainRequiredForNodeDisruptionActions` (line 131) â€” drain is required for `Reboot` or `Drain` actions; for `Special` it checks whether the registries.conf change is safe (digest-only mirrors) and skips drain if so; all other actions skip drain.\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/common/helpers.go`\n\n- `FindClosestFilePolicyPathMatch` (line 1217) â€” given a changed file path and the cluster policy file list, returns the longest matching prefix (exact path or subdirectory match). No match means the daemon defaults to `Reboot`."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1ca7e20c-f463-4aff-8411-4663c8d63aa4","uuid":"47ee9b49-1224-4ec4-831f-2a6d173ef51a","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:25:49.862Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search the machine-config-operator codebase at /home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator for:\n1. The Go type definitions for NodeDisruptionPolicy, NodeDisruptionPolicySpec, and related types (look in vendor/github.com/openshift/api or staging/src or pkg/apis)\n2. Any example YAML files or test fixtures that use nodeDisruptionPolicy in a MachineConfiguration resource\n3. The validation or defaulting logic for nodeDisruptionPolicy\n\nBe thorough â€” search in api/, vendor/, pkg/, test/, and docs/ directories. Return the full type definitions including all fields and their comments/descriptions.","agentId":"a75d9bfdacfcec099","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a comprehensive picture. Here is the complete findings report.\n\n---\n\n## NodeDisruptionPolicy Type Definitions, Examples, and Validation Logic\n\n### 1. Primary Type Definitions\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/operator/v1/types_machineconfiguration.go`\n\nAll types live in the `operator/v1` package (`opv1` alias throughout the codebase).\n\n#### Top-level anchor on `MachineConfigurationSpec` (line 58)\n```go\nNodeDisruptionPolicy NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig `json:\"nodeDisruptionPolicy\"`\n```\nComment: \"allows an admin to set granular node disruption actions for MachineConfig-based updates, such as drains, service reloads, etc. Specifying this will allow for less downtime when doing small configuration updates to the cluster. This configuration has no effect on cluster upgrades which will still incur node disruption where required.\"\n\n#### Top-level anchor on `MachineConfigurationStatus` (line 286)\n```go\nNodeDisruptionPolicyStatus NodeDisruptionPolicyStatus `json:\"nodeDisruptionPolicyStatus\"`\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig` (spec input, lines 461-480)\n```go\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig struct {\n    // files: list of MachineConfig file definitions and actions. Max 50 entries.\n    // +listType=map, +listMapKey=path, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=50\n    Files []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecFile `json:\"files\"`\n\n    // units: list of MachineConfig unit definitions and actions. Max 50 entries.\n    // +listType=map, +listMapKey=name, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=50\n    Units []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecUnit `json:\"units\"`\n\n    // sshkey: actions for all sshkey changes in the cluster\n    SSHKey NodeDisruptionPolicySpecSSHKey `json:\"sshkey\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatus` (lines 454-458)\n```go\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicyStatus struct {\n    // clusterPolicies: merge of cluster default and user provided policies\n    ClusterPolicies NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus `json:\"clusterPolicies\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus` (lines 484-500)\n```go\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus struct {\n    // +listType=map, +listMapKey=path, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=100\n    Files  []NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusFile  `json:\"files,omitempty\"`\n    // +listType=map, +listMapKey=name, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=100\n    Units  []NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusUnit  `json:\"units,omitempty\"`\n    SSHKey NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusSSHKey  `json:\"sshkey,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicySpecFile` (lines 503-521)\n```go\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecFile struct {\n    // path: location of a managed file. Actions apply to changes at this path.\n    // +required\n    Path string `json:\"path\"`\n\n    // actions: series of commands on file changes. Applied in list order.\n    // Reboot and None cannot be combined with other actions.\n    // Max 10 entries.\n    // +required, +listType=atomic, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=10\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='Reboot') ? size(self) == 1 : true\"\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"self.exists(x, x.type=='None') ? size(self) == 1 : true\"\n    Actions []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction `json:\"actions\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusFile` (lines 524-542) is structurally identical but uses `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusAction` instead, for the status side.\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicySpecUnit` (lines 544-567)\n```go\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecUnit struct {\n    // name: systemd service name. Format: ${NAME}${SERVICETYPE}, max 255 chars.\n    // ${SERVICETYPE} must be one of: .service .socket .device .mount .automount .swap\n    //   .target .path .timer .snapshot .slice .scope\n    // +required\n    Name NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName `json:\"name\"`\n\n    // actions: same rules as for files (Reboot/None standalone, max 10)\n    // +required, +listType=atomic, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=10\n    Actions []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction `json:\"actions\"`\n}\n```\n\nAgain a parallel `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusUnit` exists for the status side.\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicySpecSSHKey` / `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusSSHKey` (lines 594-626)\n```go\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecSSHKey struct {\n    // actions: same rules as files (Reboot/None standalone, max 10)\n    // +required, +listType=atomic, +kubebuilder:validation:MaxItems=10\n    Actions []NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction `json:\"actions\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction` â€” the union discriminator (lines 628-645)\n```go\n// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.type) && self.type == 'Reload' ? has(self.reload) : !has(self.reload)\"\n// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=\"has(self.type) && self.type == 'Restart' ? has(self.restart) : !has(self.restart)\"\n// +union\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction struct {\n    // type: Reboot | Drain | Reload | Restart | DaemonReload | None\n    // Reload/Restart require a corresponding reload/restart field.\n    // +unionDiscriminator, +required\n    Type NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType `json:\"type\"`\n\n    // reload: service to reload. Only valid when type==Reload.\n    // +optional\n    Reload  *ReloadService  `json:\"reload,omitempty\"`\n\n    // restart: service to restart. Only valid when type==Restart.\n    // +optional\n    Restart *RestartService `json:\"restart,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe status-side `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusAction` (lines 647-664) is the same shape but its `type` enum also includes `\"Special\"` (internal MCO action not user-settable).\n\n#### `ReloadService` / `RestartService` (lines 667-684)\n```go\ntype ReloadService struct {\n    // serviceName: full name e.g. crio.service. Same format/length rules as NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName.\n    // +required\n    ServiceName NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName `json:\"serviceName\"`\n}\n\ntype RestartService struct {\n    ServiceName NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName `json:\"serviceName\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName` â€” validated string type (lines 690-693)\n```go\n// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=`self.matches('\\\\.(service|socket|device|mount|automount|swap|target|path|timer|snapshot|slice|scope)$')`\n// +kubebuilder:validation:XValidation:rule=`self.matches('^[a-zA-Z0-9:._\\\\\\\\-]+\\\\..')`\n// +kubebuilder:validation:MaxLength=255\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName string\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType` â€” enum (lines 687-688, 695-714)\n```go\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum:=\"Reboot\";\"Drain\";\"Reload\";\"Restart\";\"DaemonReload\";\"None\"\ntype NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType string\n\nconst (\n    RebootSpecAction      NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"Reboot\"\n    DrainSpecAction       NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"Drain\"\n    ReloadSpecAction      NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"Reload\"\n    RestartSpecAction     NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"Restart\"\n    DaemonReloadSpecAction NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"DaemonReload\"\n    NoneSpecAction        NodeDisruptionPolicySpecActionType = \"None\"\n)\n```\n\n#### `NodeDisruptionPolicyStatusActionType` â€” enum (lines 719-744)\nAdds `\"Special\"` to the above set. `Special` is internal-only; users cannot set it.\n\n---\n\n### 2. YAML Example / Test Fixture\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/machineconfigurations/nodedisruptionpolicy-rebootless-path.yaml`\n\nThis is an `openshift.io/v1 Template` that produces a `MachineConfiguration`:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: template.openshift.io/v1\nkind: Template\nmetadata:\n  name: node-disruption-policy\nobjects:\n- apiVersion: operator.openshift.io/v1\n  kind: MachineConfiguration\n  metadata:\n    name: cluster\n    namespace: openshift-machine-config-operator\n  spec:\n    nodeDisruptionPolicy:\n      files:\n        - path: /home/core/test\n          actions:\n            - type: None\n```\n\nThis is the only standalone YAML file in the repository. The e2e and extended-priv tests programmatically construct `NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig` objects using the server-side apply configuration builder (`mcoac.*`) rather than static YAML.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Validation Logic\n\n#### CEL / kubebuilder validation (compile-time, in API types)\n\nAll constraints are in the type definitions above. The key rules are:\n\n- `Reboot` and `None` actions are **standalone-only** â€” CEL rules on every `Actions` field:\n  - `self.exists(x, x.type=='Reboot') ? size(self) == 1 : true`\n  - `self.exists(x, x.type=='None') ? size(self) == 1 : true`\n- `Reload` requires a `reload` sub-field; `Restart` requires a `restart` sub-field (XValidation union discriminator rules on `NodeDisruptionPolicySpecAction`).\n- `Files` and `Units` lists cap at **50 entries** in spec, **100** in status.\n- Each `Actions` list caps at **10 entries**.\n- `NodeDisruptionPolicyServiceName` is validated to match the systemd service name format (regex + MaxLength=255).\n\n#### Controller defaulting / merge logic (runtime, in MCO operator)\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/apihelpers/apihelpers.go`\n\n`MergeClusterPolicies(userDefinedClusterPolicies NodeDisruptionPolicyConfig) NodeDisruptionPolicyClusterStatus` (line 449) is the core merge function called from `pkg/operator/sync.go` line 2373 during every `syncMachineConfiguration` reconcile cycle:\n\n- Starts from hardcoded **default cluster policies** (`defaultClusterPolicies`, lines 24-194).\n- User-defined file/unit policies that **conflict** with defaults replace the default entry; otherwise they are appended.\n- If the user provides no SSH key actions, the default SSH policy is used (`NoneStatusAction`).\n- Result is stored in `MachineConfigurationStatus.NodeDisruptionPolicyStatus.ClusterPolicies`.\n\n**Default policies built into the MCO** (constants resolved from `pkg/daemon/constants/constants.go`):\n\n| Path / Unit | Default Action |\n|---|---|\n| `/var/lib/kubelet/config.json` | `None` |\n| `/etc/machine-config-daemon/no-reboot/containers-gpg.pub` | `Reload crio.service` |\n| `/etc/containers/policy.json` | `Reload crio.service` |\n| `/etc/containers/registries.conf` | `Special` (internal â€” triggers safe-merge check) |\n| `/etc/containers/registries.d` | `Reload crio.service` |\n| `/etc/crio/policies` | `Reload crio.service` |\n| `/etc/nmstate/openshift` | `None` |\n| `/etc/pki/ca-trust/source/anchors/openshift-config-user-ca-bundle.crt` | `Restart coreos-update-ca-trust.service`, then `Restart crio.service` |\n| `/etc/kubernetes/credential-providers` | `Restart kubelet.service` |\n| `/etc/systemd/system/kubelet.service.d/40-kubelet-crio-image-credential-provider.conf` | `DaemonReload`, then `Restart kubelet.service` |\n| `/etc/iri-registry` | `Restart iri-registry.service` |\n| `/usr/local/bin/load-registry-image.sh` | `Restart iri-registry.service` |\n| `/etc/pki/ca-trust/source/anchors/iri-root-ca.crt` | `Restart coreos-update-ca-trust.service` |\n| Unit `iri-registry.service` | `DaemonReload`, then `Restart iri-registry.service` |\n| SSHKey | `None` |\n\n#### Daemon action dispatch (runtime, in MCD)\n\n**File:** `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/daemon/update.go`\n\n- `calculatePostConfigChangeNodeDisruptionAction` (line 750) â€” polls until `MachineConfiguration/cluster` status is current (Generation == ObservedGeneration), then calls `calculatePostConfigChangeNodeDisruptionActionFromMCDiffs`.\n- `calculatePostConfigChangeNodeDisruptionActionFromMCDiffs` (line 655) â€” walks diff file paths using `FindClosestFilePolicyPathMatch` (longest-prefix directory match), walks diff units by exact name match,