{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_012ptANgybhpyuFQxbEsARUz", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the NodeDisruptionPolicy API. Let me help the user fill in the spec for their MachineConfiguration resource.\n\nKey things to know:\n1. The `nodeDisruptionPolicy` spec has three top-level fields: `files`, `units`, and `sshkey`\n2. Each file entry needs a `path` and `actions` list\n3. Each unit entry needs a `name` (systemd service name) and `actions` list\n4. The `sshkey` entry just needs an `actions` list\n5. Available action types: `Reboot`, `Drain`, `Reload`, `Restart`, `DaemonReload`, `None`\n6. `Reload` and `Restart` actions require specifying a `serviceName` field\n7. `Reboot` and `None` are terminal actions that can't be combined with others\n8. There are limits of 50 entries max for files and units, with up to 10 actions per entry\n\nLet me walk through a comprehensive example that demonstrates all the different action types in practice.", "signature": ""}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 3, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 4306, "cache_read_input_tokens": 33935, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 4306, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 7}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "1ca7e20c-f463-4aff-8411-4663c8d63aa4", "uuid": "b8e9071a-92d1-4620-88fa-ecb0962d582f", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcK1EhxjiYG4jos9hrv2v", "timestamp": "2026-06-22T21:25:56.737Z"}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_012ptANgybhpyuFQxbEsARUz", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Here's a complete `spec` example covering all available fields and action types:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: operator.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfiguration\nmetadata:\n  name: cluster          # must be \"cluster\" \u2014 this is a singleton resource\nspec:\n  nodeDisruptionPolicy:\n    files:\n      # Skip reboot entirely when this file changes\n      - path: /etc/myapp/config.conf\n        actions:\n          - type: None\n\n      # Reload a service (no drain, no reboot)\n      - path: /etc/myapp/tls.crt\n        actions:\n          - type: Reload\n            reload:\n              serviceName: myapp.service\n\n      # Restart a service (no drain, no reboot)\n      - path: /etc/myapp/settings.yaml\n        actions:\n          - type: Restart\n            restart:\n              serviceName: myapp.service\n\n      # Drain the node, then restart a service\n      - path: /etc/myapp/critical.conf\n        actions:\n          - type: Drain\n          - type: Restart\n            restart:\n              serviceName: myapp.service\n\n      # Reload systemd manager, then restart a service\n      - path: /etc/systemd/system/myapp.service\n        actions:\n          - type: DaemonReload\n          - type: Restart\n            restart:\n              serviceName: myapp.service\n\n      # Full node reboot (must be the only action)\n      - path: /etc/kernel/cmdline\n        actions:\n          - type: Reboot\n\n    units:\n      # Reload a unit change without rebooting\n      - name: myapp.service\n        actions:\n          - type: Reload\n            reload:\n              serviceName: myapp.service\n\n      # Restart a socket unit\n      - name: myapp.socket\n        actions:\n          - type: Restart\n            restart:\n              serviceName: myapp.socket\n\n    sshkey:\n      # Ignore SSH key changes (no disruption)\n      actions:\n        - type: None\n```\n\n**Key constraints to keep in mind:**\n\n| Rule | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| `metadata.name` | Must be `cluster` \u2014 MCO only reads the singleton |\n| `Reboot` / `None` | Must be the **only** action in the list |\n| `Reload` | Requires `reload.serviceName` |\n| `Restart` | Requires `restart.serviceName` |\n| `serviceName` format | Must end in a valid systemd suffix: `.service`, `.socket`, `.mount`, `.timer`, etc. |\n| `files` / `units` | Max **50** entries each |\n| `actions` per entry | Max **10** entries |\n\n**Action types from least to most disruptive:** `None` \u2192 `DaemonReload` \u2192 `Reload` \u2192 `Restart` \u2192 `Drain` \u2192 `Reboot`\n\nThe MCO merges your policy with its built-in defaults (e.g. `/etc/crio/*` files already default to `Reload crio.service`). If a changed file path doesn't match any policy entry, the daemon falls back to a full **Reboot**. You can see the merged result in `status.nodeDisruptionPolicyStatus.clusterPolicies` after applying."}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 3, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 4306, "cache_read_input_tokens": 33935, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 4306, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 7}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "1ca7e20c-f463-4aff-8411-4663c8d63aa4", "uuid": "491f828c-9153-4b8f-89a1-45b25cf86e48", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcK1EhxjiYG4jos9hrv2v", "timestamp": "2026-06-22T21:26:06.832Z"}
