viceName: myapp.socket\n\n    sshkey:\n      # Ignore SSH key changes (no disruption)\n      actions:\n        - type: None\n```\n\n**Key constraints to keep in mind:**\n\n| Rule | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| `metadata.name` | Must be `cluster` \u2014 MCO only reads the singleton |\n| `Reboot` / `None` | Must be the **only** action in the list |\n| `Reload` | Requires `reload.serviceName` |\n| `Restart` | Requires `restart.serviceName` |\n| `serviceName` format | Must end in a valid systemd suffix: `.service`, `.socket`, `.mount`, `.timer`, etc. |\n| `files` / `units` | Max **50** entries each |\n| `actions` per entry | Max **10** entries |\n\n**Action types from least to most disruptive:** `None` \u2192 `DaemonReload` \u2192 `Reload` \u2192 `Restart` \u2192 `Drain` \u2192 `Reboot`\n\nThe MCO merges your policy with its built-in defaults (e.g. `/etc/crio/*` files already default to `Reload crio.service`). If a changed file path doesn't match any policy entry, the daemon falls back to a full **Reboot**. You can see the merged result in `status.nodeDisruptionPolicyStatus.clusterPolicies` after applying.", "stop_reason": "end_turn", "session_id": "1ca7e20c-f463-4aff-8411-4663c8d63aa4", "total_cost_usd": 0.55582305, "usage": {"input_tokens": 6, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 7192, "cache_read_input_tokens": 64984, "output_tokens": 1394, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 7192}, "inference_geo": "", "iterations": [], "speed": "standard"}, "modelUsage": {"claude-sonnet-4-6": {"inputTokens": 495, "outputTokens": 9162, "cacheReadInputTokens": 682481, "cacheCreationInputTokens": 56577, "webSearchRequests": 0, "costUSD": 0.55582305, "contextWindow": 200000, "maxOutputTokens": 32000}}, "permission_denials": [{"tool_name": "Bash", "tool_use_id": "toolu_vrtx_01DasA2JZPQQtC9WzDyD8wfx", "tool_input": {"command": "grep -n \"nodeDisruptionPolicy